  "learn": {
    "heading": "Fractions live between the whole numbers",
    "intro": "<p>A number line has whole numbers marked: 0, 1, 2, 3… <strong>Fractions</strong> sit in the spaces between them. For example, <strong>1/2</strong> is halfway between 0 and 1. The farther right, the bigger the number.</p>",
    "examples": [
      "<strong>1/2:</strong> split the gap from 0 to 1 in two — 1/2 is the middle mark.",
      "<strong>2 1/2:</strong> go to 2, then halfway toward 3. It sits between 2 and 3."
